Package: ringdrop
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Secure, frugal P2P streamed file transfer with ring-based access control
 Ringdrop is a P2P file transfer tool built on iroh-blobs and bao protocols.
 Files are associated with rings (groups of peers); only ring members can
 download them. Transfers resume automatically if interrupted — no verified
 data is re-transferred after a crash or disconnect.
 .
 The crate is named ringdrop but the installed binary is rdrop.
